	<li><span style="font-family:Times">Moderate or severe impairment (total bilirubin &gt;1.5 x ULN and any AST): insufficient data, there are no dosage adjustments provided in the manufacturer&#39;s labeling.</span></li>
</ul>

<p><em><span style="font-family:Times">Hepatic impairment during treatment:</span></em></p>

<ul>
	<li><span style="font-family:Times">Grade 2: Temporarily withhold treatment.</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-family:Times">Grade 3 or 4: Permanently discontinue treatment. Administer systemic corticosteroids (prednisone 1 - 2 mg/kg/day [or equivalent]) followed by 1 month corticosteroid taper when LFTs show sustained improvement or return to baseline. </span></li>
